explanation: "The medial temporal lobe, especially the hippocampus, is essential for formation of declarative (explicit) memory \u2014 facts and events. Types of memory & localization:<br><br>* **Declarative (explicit) memory**: facts, events \u2192 hippocampus & medial temporal lobe\n* **Procedural (implicit) memory:** skills, habits \u2192 basal ganglia & cerebellum\n* **Associative/semantic memory storage**: neocortex\n* **Emotional memory**: amygdala<br><br>> **Clinical correlation:**\n> **Damage to medial temporal lobe (e.g., head injury) \u2192 anterograde amnesia with impaired formation of new declarative memories.**",
